unit: category
id: kprovider/gpu/drm
_name: DRM GPU Drivers

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/core
_summary: DRM core subsystem bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the DRM ioctl/GEM/vblank/atomic pipeline using bpftrace kfunc probes.
 Covers: drm_open, drm_ioctl dispatch, GET_CAP, GEM create/close,
 KMS mode resources, drm_read event queue, drm_release, vblank, and
 dma_fence_signal. Works on any driver that exposes /dev/dri/card0.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 120.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 gpu_drm_core_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/i915
_summary: Intel i915 GPU driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the i915 submission pipeline using bpftrace kfunc probes.
 Covers: i915_driver_probe, GEM context create, GEM object alloc, mmap,
 execbuffer2, i915_request_create, GuC/execlists submit, dma_fence_signal,
 request retire, GT PM wakeref, and context teardown.
 Requires an Intel GPU with the i915 module loaded.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 180.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^i915 ' /proc/modules || { echo "i915 module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_i915_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/amd
_summary: AMD amdgpu driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the amdgpu submission pipeline using bpftrace kfunc probes.
 Covers: driver probe/VERSION, AMDGPU_INFO, CTX alloc, GEM_CREATE,
 GEM_MMAP, GEM_VA, command submission (CS), amdgpu_job_run,
 dma_fence_signal, vm_flush, runtime PM, and CTX teardown.
 Requires an AMD GPU with the amdgpu module loaded.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 180.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^amdgpu ' /proc/modules || { echo "amdgpu module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_amd_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/nouveau
_summary: Nouveau (NVIDIA) GPU driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the nouveau submission pipeline using bpftrace kfunc probes.
 Covers: driver open/VERSION, GETPARAM, GEM_NEW, GEM_INFO,
 GEM_CPU_PREP/FINI, PUSHBUF dispatch, nouveau_fence_emit,
 dma_fence_signal, nvkm_subdev wakeup, bo_move, and GEM close.
 Requires an NVIDIA GPU with the nouveau module loaded.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 180.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^nouveau ' /proc/modules || { echo "nouveau module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_nouveau_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/xe
_summary: Intel Xe GPU driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the Xe driver submission pipeline using bpftrace kfunc probes.
 Covers: driver open/VERSION, DEVICE_QUERY, VM_CREATE, GEM_CREATE,
 GEM_MMAP_OFFSET, EXEC_QUEUE_CREATE, EXEC dispatch, xe_sched_job_run,
 dma_fence_signal, vm_rebind, and queue/VM teardown.
 Requires an Intel GPU with the xe module loaded (kernel >= 6.8).
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 180.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^xe ' /proc/modules || { echo "xe module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_xe_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/bridge
_summary: DRM bridge subsystem bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the DRM bridge chain lifecycle using bpftrace kprobe probes.
 Covers: bridge_add, bridge_attach, chain_mode_set, atomic pre-enable,
 enable, disable, post-disable passes, HPD notify, bridge_detach,
 and bridge_remove.
 Requires a DRM device with an active display bridge (e.g. DSI->HDMI).
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 120.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 gpu_drm_bridge_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/arm
_summary: ARM DRM display driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces ARM display engines (HDLCD, Mali-DP, Komeda) using bpftrace
 kprobe probes. Covers: platform_driver probe, drm_dev_register,
 atomic_helper_check, CRTC enable, commit_planes, vsync/IRQ,
 bridge chain enable, vblank event, modeset disables, and
 drm_dev_unregister.
 Requires an ARM SoC or QEMU with ARM display hardware.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 120.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^hdlcd \|^malidp \|^komeda ' /proc/modules || { echo "ARM display module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_arm_trace_test.py

id: kprovider/gpu/drm/nvidia-drm
_summary: NVIDIA proprietary DRM driver bpftrace workflow verification
_description:
 Traces the nvidia-drm kernel module lifecycle using bpftrace kprobe probes.
 Covers: device probe, GEM object init, atomic commit, CRTC enable,
 fence signalling, page flip, modeset, and cleanup.
 Requires NVIDIA proprietary driver with nvidia-drm module loaded.
plugin: shell
category_id: kprovider/gpu/drm
user: root
estimated_duration: 180.0
command:
 command -v bpftrace >/dev/null 2>&1 || { echo "bpftrace not found — install with: sudo apt install bpftrace"; exit 1; }
 grep -q '^nvidia_drm ' /proc/modules || { echo "nvidia_drm module not loaded — skipping"; exit 0; }
 gpu_drm_nvidia_drm_trace_test.py
